div.div:
Enhance ShopVoucherEdit with additional fields and validation
Added new fields to ShopVoucherEdit to capture assigned customer, voucher expiration and optional notes. Required validation has also been added to ensure the necessary fields are filled in. The expended UI should allow for comprehensive management of the voucher information.

Create and manage shop module with customer details
Introduced a set of database tables, models, layouts, and screens to handle customer information for the shop module. Also added features to manage voucher expiration in customer vouchers. A new route for accessing the customer list screen has been established.

Remove email sending logic from AkceChange event handler
The AkceChange event handler was simplified by removing the email sending logic. The initial design featured conditional branches for either sending a test email or iterating through all users to send an email to each one. The whole block was removed, suggesting a shift towards a different approach for handling such activity outside this event.

FIX: Update email target in AkceChange Listener
Refined the code in AkceChange and ReminderMail for more precise email targeting. Initially, mails were being sent directly to the User object, but now it's been adjusted to target the user's email attribute. Also, the ReminderMail constructor is updated to take generic parameters instead of specific object types.

FIX: Correct email sending logic in EventsEditScreen
Changed the logic in EventsEditScreen for sending a confirmation mail. Previously, mails were sent to 'vakea@fluffici.eu' when not in 'APP_TEST_MAIL' environment, which was incorrect. The logic has been switched; now 'vakea@fluffici.eu' receives emails only in 'APP_TEST_MAIL' environment, and in other cases, all users receive the mail.
